Yes, that makes sense to me.  And, I agree that worship takes on many forms.  I guess the difference in my experience is that I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>didn't always</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> have the sense that it was a reverent service.  In fact, my upbringing within the church led me to dismiss the need for corporate worship; I came to the conclusion that it was SO casual, and SO individualized, that I could do so on my own (and not have to put up with the peeps who turned me off from church! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ).<br>
