<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>So, I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>guess</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I'd go with it's the heart. God knows our attitude. I'd say our heart influences our actions more than the other way round.... hm.. but on the other hand... people tend to go with what they learn as children, what they grow up with being comfortable. (that is IF they grow up IN a church)  <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yeah, and I don't want to come off as being judgmental here; I think it's a good thing that we have a variety of denominations so that different personalities can worship God as they see fit, but at the same time, I wonder at God's perspective in some services.  <br>
<br>
For example, some of the services I have attended over the years ran more like a business meeting than a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>worship</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> service.  That led to my mind wandering...or I would sit there and read my bible and then miss what the preacher started talking about.  <br>
<br>
Is it all subjective or is there a line to be drawn at what is acceptable and pleasing to God, as illustrated in Malachi?<br>
