<br>
I think you CAN do it on your own. Not everyone is in a situation where they can attend a church service. I think one's own personal prayer time can be as reverent as services in a cathedral. Maybe that's why I think it's the heart that's the most important. <br>
<br>
I mean, if you've a bunch of folks that don't really have their heart towards God, well, even if they are in a church like setting, it's STILL not the same as a group of true believers in a not so church like setting. Does that make sense? Did I explain it right?<br>
<br>
And I think that fellowship is just as important a form of &quot;worship&quot; too. <br>
<br>
&lt;some of the services I have attended over the years ran more like a business meeting than a worship service. That led to my mind wandering...or I would sit there and read my bible and then miss what the preacher started talking about.&gt;<br>
<br>
I think this is that &quot;personality&quot; thing. Some people are not as warm, personally, as others. It's like hugging... some people just assume that EVERYone is going to hug everyone else.. I'm not like that. I don't like hugging strangers. So for me, that's an uncomfortable situation. But for others, it's just peachy! <br>
<br>
And if, even while in a service, your reading the Bible gives you something different than what's going on with the pastor, then God's meeting <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>your</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> needs where they are. Who says it's ONLY what the pastor is on about is what God has for us?<br>
<br>
&lt;Is it all subjective or is there a line to be drawn at what is acceptable and pleasing to God&gt;<br>
<br>
I'd say it's more subjective than not. We know in our hearts if something being presented is just wrong. God knows our hearts too. And even if some guy is all eloquent but it's balderdash as far as doctrine goes, THAT's not what God wants. He wants our hearts towards Him. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:fuchsia;font-family:comic sans ms;font-size:x-small;">....·´¨¨))</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;font-family:comic sans ms;font-size:small;">-:¦:-</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:teal;font-family:comic sans ms;font-size:x-small;"> <br>
