I have rarely seen Baptism and the Lord's Supper emphasized too much. In general Protestant churches these are almost an after thought. Over the years in pastoring (in Lutheran congregations), wherever I taught the Scriptures, the congregation inevitably desired communion/Lord's Supper every week (that is the &quot;norm&quot; for Lutherans according to the Book of Concord). So within two years the congregations celebrated the Lord's Supper at every service. In the process people learned the value, joy, awesome-ness of this &quot;event.&quot; Public worship without the Lord's Supper seemed incomplete. <p>In Christ,<br>
